Package FOMS.process_manager

Class ProcessOrder

  • java.lang.Object
    • FOMS.process_manager.ProcessOrder
  • public class ProcessOrder
extends java.lang.Object
    The ProcessOrder class provides functionality to process orders based on order ID. It allows updating the status of an order and persisting those changes to a file. This class is also responsible for starting and canceling a cancellation timer based on order status changes.

      • processOrderID

        public static java.util.List<Order> processOrderID​(java.lang.String orderIdToFind,
                                                   java.lang.String status)
        Processes an order by ID, updates its status, and optionally manages a cancellation timer. It then saves the updated order list to a file.
        Parameters:
        orderIdToFind - The ID of the order to process.
        status - The new status to set for the order.
        Returns:
        A list of Order objects reflecting the updated state, or null if no matching order is found.

      • saveOrderListToFile

                                       java.lang.String filename)
        Saves the list of orders to the specified file.
        Parameters:
        ordersList - A list of Order objects to save.
        filename - The path of the file where the orders are to be saved.
